; @WriteLineInt32 : (i32) -> void
;
; Prints a signed 32-bit integer in decimal followed by CR (which osasci
; expands to CR/LF). Ported from
; DotNetro.Compiler.CodeGen.BbcMicroCodeGenerator.CompileSystemConsoleWriteLineInt32.
;
; WHY TARGET MIR (not generic dialects): the magnitude loop needs an i32 value
; that is simultaneously loaded from / stored to memory AND run through a
; multi-byte subtract inside a loop. Expressed generically, that overruns the
; (spill-free) linear-scan register allocator — four live accumulator bytes
; exceed the single $a register, and a loop-carried i32 can't be threaded as a
; wide block argument either. So this is hand-written, fully-lowered MOS6502
; MIR; the pipeline passes it through unchanged (isel passes mos6502.* ops
; through; AMS only refines pre-AMS forms; pseudo-expansion sees no copies).
;
; Algorithm (no division): keep the working value in zero-page slots zp4..zp7
; (lo..hi). If the MSB's sign bit is set, print '-' and two's-complement
; negate. Then, for each power of ten 1e9 down to 1 (unrolled, the constant
; loaded into zp9..zp12), repeatedly subtract the power while the value is
; >= it (32-bit SEC/SBC, BCS to keep + INX the digit counter, else ADC the
; power back). The pad flag (zp8) suppresses leading zeros; the
; printed-something flag (zp13) forces a final '0' when the value was zero.
